Description: Green glazed composition amulet in the form of a one sided right wedjat-eye, pierced lengthwise, with only black brow and pupil represented in low relief (no other detail).
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.60, p.180, pl.22)
Condition: fair - lower part broken and missing, black pupil erased.
